At the start of the year we set a goal to make 2022 our best year ever. And I'm glad to say we kept our New Year's resolution. 
This meant we wanted to have more "firsts"
First times hitting business & financial goals
Firsts with new experiences which we did visiting new places like Dubai, Perth, Adelaide, and other Australian cities we hadn't been to before.
Firsts with our personal & fitness journey...
First time meeting our little Kobe.
And sharing more firsts with our friends & family...

My morning routine never changes even when on vacay 🌴

How I stay on track even on holidays:

🤍 always strive to do my best, not for perfection

🤍 mindful but balanced eating but remembering you only live once! 
🤍 always be kind to yourself, knowing life will resume once I'm home!

🤍 MY SALMON CRISPY RICE 🤍

One of my favourite appetizers to make, tasty and so simple 🍣
I always get asked how I get the rice so perfectly Square so thought it would be easier to show you...

This is how I get them PERFECTLY crispy and square everytime!

Sushi rice
- 1 cup with 1.5 cup water, cook as instructed 
Once cooked add:
- 1tsp sugar (I use equal)
- dash of rice vinegar 

The trick here is to use a square 8x8 cake tin lined in cling wrap so you can press the rice down with your hands, then I freeze (normally I make the rice in the morning before cooking in the PM).

When you remove the rice from freezer let it defrost for about 15min and use a knife that's been wet with hot water, it will cut very easily if you do this step.

When frying I just eyeball to see browning of the rice edges, before I flip. Use whatever oil you like but be careful, it will spit! 

Spicy salmon topping,
- 1 salmon sashimi grade fillet diced
- Siracha (chilli powder optional if you like things extra hot)
- kewpi Mayo
- sesame oil (tiny bit)

I like Avo 🥑 on mine and I garnish with sesame seeds but you can use shallots; japlepenos, chilli, whatever you like!!

This recipe makes 16 pieces and it's really filling so can easily feed 2-4 people 🤍

Tag me if you give this a try 😘 and leave a comment if you have a question 🤍⬇️ #salmoncrispyrice #easyrecipes #foodstagram

1 MONTH... SURPRISSSSSEEE💍 
It's always been you and me against the world,
So eloping always felt like the most natural way to celebrate our love. Perfect doesn't even begin to describe this moment🤍💒👰‍♀️🤵‍♂️you are all I've ever wanted and I am forever on cloud 9 ☁️ ♾️

** kept this on the DL for many reasons; I didn't want pressure added until it was done, I wanted it to be as low key and private as possible, I just wanted it to be about us 2 etc etc. 
I waited until we got home to tell our loved ones, and now the cat is out of the bag I can openly say, eloping was 1000% the best choice for us (I was worried about feeling guilty initially for not telling everyone of our plans). Highly recommend if it's on the table for you 😚🤍💯🫶🏼 and yes, I had 4 dresses for the occasion 🤪 the only thing missing was our baby boys, but other than that. It was more than we had dreamed of, besides, nothing gets more private than getting married in secret on a private island 😂

Ran away and married my best friend in secret 🤫 
Broke many traditions,
On a private island resort.
And NGL it was one of the best decisions we had ever made.
Having a big wedding never felt right to me personally,
I never envisioned myself as a traditional bride.
Especially being a Vietnamese Catholic, with mammoth families on both sides.
So we finally did what was not expected of us.
And eloped 💍🤍💒
Big or small wedding, I hope you do what makes you happy, what makes sense to you both as a couple,
What you've always dreamt of,
and not what other people want or expect of you.
It's your love story! You should be able to celebrate it as you wish! 💫
I did a Q&A which included cost breakdown; how we did it and dove a little more as to why - saved in my highlights 🤍#weddingdress #elopement #weddinginspo

My first car was a Mazda 121, my dad helped me get it, it was $1000.
It didn't have aircon or electric windows.
And one day I was driving to school, stopped at the lights and a truck speeding 40km/hr above the limit, lost control of the truck and rear ended me.
That car saved me.
When I met Jimi he drove a red Hyundai i30.
We fell in love when he had that car.
From a young age my parents knew I was "good" at school, (I was probably more than good) they put a lot of pressure on me to go to University so I could have a better life then they had and could give me.
Both had said to me on separate occasions "you need to be successful because we have nothing to leave you when we go."
I did everything I was meant to, straight A's, scholarships, Uni & while doing my Masters of Medical Ultrasound, I knew they had such a huge sense of relief.
They were proud.
And I knew when I decided I wasn't going go to my placement in Canberra to take a completely different route and follow the lead of a man I loved - who also didn't have much to "give" me at the time...
They were shocked.
How could they not be disappointed or worried? Especially my mum.
And I know so many people around me, doubted my decision, they didn't believe in us.
From that day Jimi and I have been working tirelessly to build our life - to prove to everyone it was in fact, the right choice for me.
They probably still don't understand what I/ we do (the online space is still so new to their generation) and that's ok because I was determined to show them how a woman can  share the same destination-path as her partner and still be successful, strong & independent at the same time. Sometimes, when working I'm at home, with my boys by my side, I am so overcome with happiness it almost feels surreal.
This is just a car, it's an object or a material item to most,
But to us it represents so much more, 
It's just another milestone, 
And we have so many more to look forward to

Under $20 headphone refresh 🎧
These 2 pairs are about 5 years old. The gold pair has gone through this make over twice where as the black is having it's first.
It's a really fast, easy and money saving hack since the sound from both is still in tact. And we love money saving hacks 😜
Steps below and if you want the link to the replacement pads, comment below "me please" and I'll send them over 🎁

Step 1️⃣
Remove the old padding using a butter knife. Slide between the plastic of the headphones and the padding and start to pry open. 
Its much easier the second time around and you may have to use a bit of force around the circumference if this is your first time because this is when the adhesive is strongest.

Step 2️⃣
Remove all remaining adhesive. If this is your first time this probably might take some effort depending on the condition of your headphones. I use alcohol wipes and tweezers. Once the plastic is completely clean I wipe over with water to ensure the surface is completely clean and dry for the new padding to adhere well.

Step 3️⃣
Remove the backing sticker of your new pads and check you have matched left with right sides before adhering down. Match the little  holes in the replacements to the little plastic "bits" of your headphones if they have them. (They just are 2 little plastic pieces that stick out) They should then click into place but not every model has them so just check beforehand!

**The black pair also started peeling on the outer sides where the b's are so I decided just to peel them completely off for a cleaner appearance!

Done! ✅ Hope that helps you save yourself from resorting to purchasing a brand new pair!!! ❤️
